y gave the best results. The marrow\nviscosity is identified as the crucial reference to categorize bone cements as\nhigh- or low- viscosity in the context of vertebroplasty. It is confirmed that\na cement with higher viscosity than the marrow ensures stable development of\nthe injection and a proper cement interdigitation inside the vertebra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Sep 2022 09:31:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 12 May 2023 15:08:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-15"}
