cialists from\nmultiple disciplines. Results: We found that there are many similarities in\nwhat researchers and support specialists want and think about data discovery,\nboth in social sciences and in other disciplines. There are, however, some\ndifferences which we have identified, most notably the interconnection of data\ndiscovery with web search, literature search and social networks. Conclusion:\nWe conclude by proposing recommendations for how different types of support\nwork can address these points of difference to better support researchers' data\ndiscovery practices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Sep 2022 09:36:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Feb 2023 17:20:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-10"}
